oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Church Street viaduct overlooking the North Gulch area, Nashville, Tennessee, 2015 October 05
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A view of the North Gulch area, pictured from the Church Street Viaduct, Nashville, Tennessee, October 5th, 2015. The viaduct was built in the 1990s, after replacing an earlier structure that was built to carry car traffic over the railroad tracks. Forms part of the Leanne Garland Photograph Collection. 1 digital photograph.
